The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, August 08, 2004 				Metro Recommends
THE VCD
	(MusicWorld, Rs 299) Featuring some of the biggest names of Hollywoods golden era, this classic brings Leo Tolstoys masterpiece to vibrant reel life. Audrey Hepburn, Henry Fonda and Mel Ferrer render compelling performances in this spectacular tale of tragic romance set in the backdrop of Napoleons invasion of Russia. THE TALK
	(British Council, 7 pm on August 9) The panel discussion involving Susheila Naasta, David Dabydeen, Mini Krishnan and Amit Chaudhuri will probe hostile divisions, cultural translations and migratory writing. THE LAUNCH				 																																	(Apeejay House, 7 pm on August 9) Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will launch this collection of Mrinal Sens memoirs. The film-makers trip down memory lane, from Naxalite Bengal to modern-day loneliness, is something both cine-buffs and social commentators have been waiting for. 
